EmailTemplate.name: CIA - Tracking Welcome Pack
EmailTemplate.subject: [Tracking Welcome Pack]
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Thank you for your recent enquiry in to Australia Post business services.
To help you integrate with our Track Items API please access the technical specifications in our Developer Centre.
The Track Items testbed can be accessed via https://digitalapi.auspost.com.au/testbed/shipping/v1/track?tracking_ids={tracking_ids}
The live Track Items production environment can be accessed via https://digitalapi.auspost.com.au/shipping/v1/track?tracking_ids={tracking_ids}
Technical notes:
1) The Track Items API is rate limited to 10 requests per minute. You may include up to 10 tracking IDs with each request.
2) In the testbed, the below scenarios will return tracking results. The responses in the Testbed are pre-configured and return test data only.
a) If tracking_ids string length is 13 characters than we return an article result – e.g. ABC1234567890
b) If tracking_ids string length is 23 characters than we return a barcode result - e.g. ABC12345678901234567890
I have also provided you with access to the Validate Suburb API. You can find more information about this API here in our Developer Centre including details or the production environment URL.
If you have any queries regarding this information, please don’t hesitate to contact us at customer_connectivity@auspost.com.au.
Regards
Lodgement & APIs Team
Parcels, eCommerce and Digital
